Description_lang: This booming coastal city is run by Baron Revilgaz of the Blackwater Raiders.  Mortal enemies of the Bloodsail Buccaneers and part of the Steamwheedle Cartel.
This Alliance capital is the pride of the Dun Morogh dwarves.  Home to King Magni.
The former denizens of Gnomeregan, now living in New Tinkertown and in league with the Alliance.
The dwarves of the Thorium Brotherhood epitomize excellence in craftsmanship and are bent on unlocking the secrets of Blackrock Mountain.
Led by Sylvanas Windrunner, the Forsaken have joined a tenuous alliance with the Horde and established this capital in the vast depths under the Ruins of Lordaeron.
This Alliance capital is populated by Night Elves and is located in the Island of Teldrassil.  Ruled by the Priestess of the Moon, Tyrande Whisperwind.
A primarily human criminal organization that operates mostly out of the Alterac Mountains and Hillsbrad Foothills.
One of the last bastions of human power, this Alliance capital is ruled by the young but wise king, Anduin Wrynn.
Founded by Thrall, this Horde capital city is home to many of the proud orc clans of Durotar.
Baine Bloodhoof leads his people, the proud Tauren, from this mighty Horde capital.
These bloodthirsty corsairs are the bane of many a merchant in the high seas.  Sworn enemies of Booty Bay.
These centaur have made their home in the southern region of Desolace.  Mortal enemies of the Magram Centaur.
These centaur have made their home in the eastern region of Desolace.  Mortal enemies of the Gelkis Centaur.
These trolls have come to Yojamba Isle in an effort to recruit help against the resurrected Blood God and his Atal'ai Priests in Zul'Gurub.
This guild of thieves and assassins welcomes only those of extraordinary prowess into its fold.  Sworn rivals of the Syndicate.
Capital of the Steamwheedle Cartel and home to goblinhood's finest engineers, alchemists and merchants.
Part of the Steamwheedle Cartel, this goblin city provides a neutral haven for those that wish to trade goods and services in the Barrens.
The League of Arathor seeks to reclaim the lost land of Arathi Basin for their benefactors in Stormwind.
The Defilers seek to claim Arathi Basin's valuable resources for the Horde.
An organization focused on protecting Azeroth from the threat of the Scourge.  Strongholds of the Argent Dawn can be found in the Eastern and Western Plaguelands.
This tribe of exiled trolls has joined forces with Thrall and the Horde.  They now call Durotar their home, which they share with their orc allies.
As the last uncorrupted furbolg tribe, the Timbermaw seek to preserve their spiritual ways and end the suffering of their brethren.
This trading post is run by the goblins of the Steamwheedle Cartel and it sits in the crossroads of Winterspring's main trade routes.
This small group of reclusive night elves raises and trains wintersabers in the Winterspring area.
The druids of Cenarion Circle are guardians of nature and make their home in tranquil Moonglade.
The Frostwolf Clan seeks to drive out the dwarves of the Stormpike Expedition from Alterac Valley.
The Stormpike Dwarves have set up residence in Alterac Valley, where they're locked in battle with the Frostwolf Orcs.
These elementals have made their home on the islands east of Azshara.  Sworn enemies of the armies of Ragnaros.
A remnant of the once powerful elves living in Dire Maul, yet still wise and knowledgeable about great secrets.
Fierce orcs of the Warsong Clan, locked in battle against the Silverwing Sentinels in Warsong Gulch.
Staunch defenders of Ashenvale, locked in battle against the Warsong Outriders in Warsong Gulch.
A carnival that showcases the weird and the extraordinary, located on a mysterious island only accessible for the first week of every month.
The descendants of the Bronze Dragonflight are the guardians of time and care little for the mortal races.
The capital of Quel'Thalas, home of the blood elves.  Though nearly destroyed by Arthas' attack on the Sunwell, Silvermoon is once again a thriving city.

Once a high elf town, Tranquillien became abandoned after the Scourge invaded Quel'Thalas.  It has now been reclaimed by the Forsaken and the blood elves who seek to rid the Ghostlands of the Scourge.
The naaru vessel that brought the draenei to Azeroth.  Though stranded in the Azuremyst Isles, it acts as a home city for this noble race.

An ancient order of draenei priests once run by Velen, the Aldor are currently led by High Priestess Ishanah.  They are servants of the naaru in Shattrath City known as the Sha'tar.  Rivals of the Scryers.
Led by Nexus-Prince Haramad, the Consortium is a loosely affiliated cartel of ethereal smugglers, traders and thieves that has come to Outland to benefit from its riches.
Voren'thal the Seer leads the dissident blood elves who've rejected Kael'thas' path to power.  They've joined forces with the naaru of Shattrath City, much to the dismay of the Aldor.
The Sha'tar are a group of powerful naaru who rule over a rebuilt Shattrath City.  With the help of the Aldor and the Scryers, they lead the battle against Illidan and the Burning Legion.
This reclusive group of brown-skinned orcs has escaped any form of demonic corruption.  They have retained their traditional way of life in the face of great changes in Outland.
An exploratory force sent to Outland by the Cenarion Circle to study surviving life forms.  The Cenarion Expedition has quickly gained in size and autonomy since the opening of the Dark Portal.

Vestiges of the Sons of Lothar, veterans of the Alliance that first came into Draenor, have steadfastly held on to this Hellfire outpost.  They are now joined by the armies from Stormwind and Ironforge.
The expedition sent through the Dark Portal by Thrall has built a stronghold in Hellfire Peninsula.  Thrallmar serves as a base of operations for much of the Horde's activities in Outland.
A secret sect of the Kirin Tor founded to spy on Medivh and his activities.
The sporelings are a mostly peaceful race of mushroom-men native to Outland. Their home is located in the southern bogs of Zangarmarsh.
Draenei for "redeemed."  These Broken have escaped the grasp of their various slavers in Outland and have made their home in Nagrand.  It is there that they seek to rediscover their destiny.
The Keepers of Time are bronze dragons hand-picked by Nozdormu to watch over the Caverns of Time.
A secretive subgroup of the Bronze Dragonflight, led by Soridormi, prime mate of Nozdormu.
Used for the Blackheart the Inciter event.
Used for the Blackheart the Inciter event.
Used for the Blackheart the Inciter event.
Used for the Blackheart the Inciter event.
Used for the Blackheart the Inciter event.
The refugees of Shattrath come from diverse backgrounds and races.  Word of helpful deeds spreads quickly among the Denizens of Lower City.
The elite of the Broken tribe known as the Ashtongue, officially aligned with Illidan. The Deathsworn are Akama's most trusted lieutenants and are privy to their leader's mysterious motivations.

This unusual brood of dragons was spawned from the eggs of Deathwing's black dragonflight, and infused with raw nether-energies.  Now, they seek to find their identity beyond the shadows of their father's destructive heritage.
An airborne military force created by Shattrath City to deal with the threats that loom in the highest reaches of Outland.
The combined forces of the Alliance in Northrend, lead by the Valiance Expedition, but also including civilian groups such as the Explorer's League.
The enlightened denizens of Ogri'la have made their dwelling in the western Blade's Edge Mountains, where proximity to apexis crystals has caused them to transcend their brutish ogre nature.
The main armies of the Alliance in Northrend, moving against the Scourge and unified under King Varian Wrynn's command.
The combined forces of the Horde in Northrend, spearheaded by the Warsong Offensive.
These hardy people are cousins of the Tauren and have become valuable scouts for the armies of the Horde as they march northward.
The Forsaken tasked by Sylvanas Windrunner with enacting Undercity's vengeance against Arthas by delivering the latest strain of their deadly Plague.
This organization seeks to find the origin of the dwarven race by collecting Titan artifacts.  Their most recent research has led them to various archeological sites in Northrend.
A test faction.

The tuskarr are a tough but peaceful people who derive their livelihood from fishing and whaling.  Their settlements have recently come under fierce attack and welcome any allies who would come to their aid.
Shattrath City's final push against Prince Kael'thas' operations in the Sunwell.
Garrosh Hellscream commands the Horde's main expeditionary forces as they make their way into Northrend to face Arthas and the armies of the Scourge.
The mages and archmages running the city of Dalaran.  Faced with the rising threats of the Blue Dragonflight and the Scourge, they've transported their city to the heart of Northrend.
With the Blue Dragonflight's violent upheaval against all mortal users of magic, the remaining dragonflights have banded under the leadership of the Red Dragonflight to combat their wayward kin.
A militant core of high elves that rejects the admission of blood elves into the Kirin Tor.  They've united under the banner of Vereesa Windrunner and joined the Alliance forces in Northrend.
Freed from the grasp of the Lich King, his former Death Knights have regrouped against him under the banner of Highlord Darion Mograine.

Driven from their lands by the Scourge, this fierce tribe of wolvar stumbled upon Sholazar Basin, where they intend to make their new home.  Their aggressive nature has put them at odds with the various gorloc tribes known collectively as the Oracles.

The gorlocs of Sholazar Basin are a race of reptilian creatures who see themselves as guardians of the titan technology that remains in the zone (though they understand little of it).  They find themselves in an escalating territorial war with the wolvar.
Led by Tirion Fordring, the Argent Crusade combines the reformed Order of the Silver Hand with the Argent Dawn in one final push against the forces of the Lich King.
The frost giants of the Storm Peaks are a war-like race that makes their home in Dun Niffelem.

Traditionally barred from Dalaran, the Horde has been accepted into the city through the efforts of Archmage Aethas Sunreaver.  His followers have taken up his name and watch over the ward known as Sunreaver's Sanctuary.
This mysterious race of frost dwarves makes their home in the Storm Peaks.  They've recently befriended members of the Explorers' League and welcome Alliance members within their settlements.

Run by the ruthless Trade Prince Gallywix, the Bilgewater Cartel is the most powerful trading company on the Isle of Kezan. From their headquarters at Bilgewater Port, the cartel dominates trade all over the South Seas.
The people of Gilneas are a nation of survivors.  Having walled themselves off from the rest of humanity, they must now face new threats from within.

This gathering of the most powerful shaman of Azeroth seeks to maintain the balance between the world's elemental forces.  Their main focus during the cataclysm has been to  repair and stabilize the damage caused by Deathwing's arrival.

Under a pact by Tirion Fordring and Darion Mograine, the Argent Crusade and the Knights of the Ebon Blade have set aside their differences during the attack on Icecrown Citadel until the Lich King is slain.

Faced with the impending devastation of Mount Hyjal, the most powerful members of the Cenarion Circle have joined forces with their Emerald Dragonflight allies to fend off Ragnaros' elemental hordes and the Twilight's Hammer.
Guild reputation is your personal standing with your guild, and is required to buy guild rewards.  Guild reputation is gained automatically when you earn guild experience.

The elemental plane of earth, Deepholm, is ruled by Therazane and her children, the Stone Lords.  After witnessing the devastation Deathwing and his followers caused her realm, Therazane treats all outsiders with open hostility.

This wayward orc clan was once empowered by Deathwing himself to enslave red dragons, including Alexstrasza.  Currently less numerous and powerful, the Dragonmaw make their home in the Twilight Highlands.

The cat-like people of Ramkahen are the descendants of the Tol'vir, guardians of Uldum.  Though they've lost their stone bodies, protecting the secrets of the titans is still a part of their rigid tradition.

The Wildhammer dwarves are known for their near-reckless courage as well as their unsurpassed gryphon-riding skills.  After losing their home of Grim Batol to a Dark Iron Curse, they've spread their dwellings around the Twilight Highlands.

Once led by Duke Reginald Baradin II, this fierce army has historic ties to the island stronghold of Tol Barad.  They have joined the forces of the Alliance in an effort to repeal the Horde invaders and gain control of this strategic island.

Hellscream's Reach is an elite Horde regiment comprised solely of veterans of multiple tours of duty.   Handpicked by Garrosh himself, he has commanded them to take complete control of Tol Barad.  Failure is not an option.
Infuriated by the destruction wrought by the Lord of Flame, the Cenarion Circle seize the initiative, fighting back against Ragnaros and driving deep into the very heart of the Firelands.
For nearly three generations, the esteemed Shang Xi has prepared pandaren heroes for lives of adventure.
A spirited, violent, and short-lived race of monkey people

Name_lang: CoT Well of Eternity - High Elves
CoT Well of Eternity - Demon Balls
CoT Well of Eternity - Hunter Stalkers

Description_lang: A reserved, methodical race of fish people.
A noble and spirited tribe of Monkey people.
The evil spirits of the land.
A remnant of the once powerful elves living in Dire Maul, yet still wise and knowledgeable about great secrets.
The ancient progenitors of this land, the Mogu hate any and all pretenders, including the upstart Pandaren.
This mysterious society of Pandaren intend to solve the Mogu problem once and for all.
The shadowy protectors of Pandaria's temples, the Shado-Pan are wrought with mystery.
Guardians of the East Temple
The Tillers are peaceful and productive pandaren, working with the land to feed the massive appetites of their people.
Jogu's easy to find - gazing into the bottom of a bottle of the cheapest Stormstout Brewery has to offer.
Ella aspires to be a great brewer, but she has a long road ahead of her!
Old Hillpaw is the canniest chicken raiser around.
If you've ever had a question about sheep, Chee Chee will know the answer.
A stout, proud defender of the farmlands, Sho is always there when you need a strong fist.
The respected leader of the Tillers, Haohan Mudclaw is swamped with responsibilities.
Tina Mudclaw is fond of the delicate things in life.
Managing the Halfhill Market makes Gina Mudclaw one stressed lady!
Fish Fellreed's found out more about the history of this land than the rest of the town's forgotten.
Farmer Fung grows the biggest vegetables in the Heartland!
The Anglers are a group of Pandaren fisherman that hope to feed their people and grow their knowledge of fishing.
The ravening swarms of the Mantid roam the Towlong Steppes and Dread Wastes, crushing all in their path.
These Mantid Elders are untouched by the corruption and insanity that has overtaken the remainder of the Mantid Swarm. They seek to work with the races of Pandaria to restore their Queen to glory.
These brave Pandaren defend the temples of Pandaria from the evils of the Sha.
Caretakers of the mysteries of Pandaria, these brave souls roam the continent, hoping to learn from their history.
These noble Pandaren safeguard the secrets of hereditary brews, braving great hardship to construct their potent concoctions.
Led by the intrepid Ji Firepaw, the Huojin Pandaren are quick to act and quicker to fight for what they believe in.
Led by the stalwart Aysa Cloudsinger, the Tushui Pandaren believe in contemplation and reasoned action.
5.0 Cooking - This is a hidden faction used to level up Nomi.
The consummate fisherman and lover of fine alcohol from across the land, Nat's irascible exterior belies a love of teaching.
Black Prince Wrathion is the last of the black dragons. He has been known to richly reward those who earn his trust and support his endeavors.
The first season of the Horde Brawler's Guild occurred during the Pandaria campaign.
Horde forces in Pandaria, stationed at Domination Point in Krasarang Wilds.
Alliance forces in Pandaria, stationed at Lion's Landing in Krasarang Wilds.
Ignited by Jaina's fury, the Kirin Tor Offensive seek to seize Thunder Isle for the glory of the Alliance!
Outcast from Dalaran, the Sunreaver Onslaught fight to obtain powerful mogu artifacts from among the ruins of Thunder Isle, and to secure their future if the Horde falls to anarchy.
Akama is distrustful of Warlocks after witnessing Illidan's fall to his own corruption, followed by the invasion of the Black Temple by Warlocks after the Cataclysm.
The first season of the LFG Brawler's Guild occurred during the Pandaria campaign.

Name_lang: Monster, Enforced Neutral For Force Reaction

Description_lang: These valorous Shado-Pan venture into the Throne of Thunder to vanquish the evil found within, and exact justice for the centuries of slavery they endured under the Thunder King's reign.
Vol'jin has declared open rebellion against Garrosh Hellscream. With the aid of both Horde and Alliance forces, he gathers resources in preparation for an attack on Orgrimmar itself.
The Frostwolf orcs of Frostfire Ridge are a tight-knit family of brutal warriors, well equipped to deal with the savage realities of Draenor.
The Timewalkers guard the timeways from those who would take advantage of the bronze dragonflight's mortality; most are adventurers or scholars that have previously worked with the Keepers of Time.
Shaohao, the long lost Emperor of the Pandaren people, is a personage worthy of deep respect.
Frostfire ogres are not interesting, but they do like to argue.
You've been corrupted by the power of Ordos, and have turned against your friends and foes in mindless rage.
Worshippers of the dread god Rukhmar, these vile filth seek to stain the world with the blood of their foes.
Working from the shadows, the Arakkoa Outcasts seek to bring a brighter tomorrow.
A tenuous alliance of many of the orc clans of Draenor under the leadership of Grommash Hellscream.
Twisted in the service of the Shadow Council, these draenei have sacrificed much in pursuit of power.
Highmaul ogres like togas and gladiator fights.
Horde forces in Ashran, stationed at Warspear.
Alliance forces in Ashran, stationed at Stormshield.
The second season of the Horde Brawler's Guild occurred during the Draenor campaign.
The second season of the Alliance Brawler's Guild occurred during the Draenor campaign.
The Laughing Skull clan calls the most savage reaches of Draenor home, laughing maniacally at the impending annihilation they face from every side.
The defenders of Shattrath struggle to regain control of their capital city, having been betrayed from within.
The goblins of the Steamwheedle Preservation Society seek to liberate relics from the ogres of Nagrand with the noble intention of selling them to the highest bidder.
Under the leadership of five powerful exarchs, the draenei of Draenor have prospered in a savage world.
Draenor is a long of infinite opportunity, and very little competition.
Your personal bodyguard, stationed at your barracks. You can build friendship with Delvar by inviting him to fight alongside you.
Station bodyguards at your barracks.
Your personal bodyguard, stationed at your barracks. You can build friendship with Tormmok by inviting him to fight alongside you.
Your personal bodyguard, stationed at your barracks. You can build friendship with Ishaal by inviting him to fight alongside you.
Your personal bodyguard, stationed at your barracks. You can build friendship with Illona by inviting her to fight alongside you.
Your personal bodyguard, stationed at your barracks. You can build friendship with Vivianne by inviting her to fight alongside you.
Your personal bodyguard, stationed at your barracks. You can build friendship with Aeda by inviting him to fight alongside you.
Your personal bodyguard, stationed at your barracks. You can build friendship with Leorajh by inviting him to fight alongside you.
Highmaul ogres like togas and gladiator fights.
Demons from places unknown and unrivaled in power.
The Highmountain Tribe has dwindled in numbers over the years, and with the drogbar threat looming, seek new allies to save their homeland.
If you have to ask, you're already dead.
Yrel has assembled the remaining Exarchs and is calling for a crusade in Velen's name. Together they are working to establish a foothold in Tanaan Jungle and to overthrow Gul'dan.
Seeking to protect Azeroth with a decisive victory on Draenor, Warchief Vol'jin is assembling an elite team of champions to establish a foothold in Tanaan Jungle and to overthrow Gul'dan.
Survivors of a grisly civil war, these beleaguered arakkoans hope the reclamation of apexis artifacts will hold the key to peacefully rebuilding their civilization.
The treacherous wilds of Tanaan Jungle have attracted the craftiest hunters from both Azeroth and Draenor. To defeat the beasts of Tanaan, one must become a beast.
These exiled Nightborne elves suffer withdrawals after being cut off from the Nightwell. They oppose their people's alliance with the Legion and fight for some kind of redemption.
First Arcanist Thalyssra
DEPRECATED
Chief Telemancer Oculeth
The druids and their allies in Val'sharah have guarded the Emerald Dream since time immemorial.

After Legion forces broke the Vault of the Wardens with the aid of Gul'dan, what few Wardens remain are determined to rebuild their prison and hunt down the terrifying beasts that were let loose when it fell.
The Night Time is the Right Time [PH]
The ghostly Court of Farondis and its allies continue the fight against an onslaught of invaders on the cursed island of Azsuna.
Arcanist Valtrois
Elves that have sworn themselves to fighting against the Burning Legion, no matter the cost.
These are the chosen warriors of Odyn, sworn to his service in life and death.
Once a student of the Kirin Tor, Margoss has turned to fishing to ease his stressful life.

High in their floating home city of Dalaran, Olisarra and Angelique treat the injured, the sick and the quite nearly, fatally wounded. They also sell wares to travelers who are in need of medical supplies.
The third season of the Horde Brawler's Guild occurred during the Broken Isles campaign.
The third season of the Alliance Brawler's Guild occurred during the Broken Isles campaign.
Allies of the demigod Aviana and protectors of the winged creatures of the Broken Isles.
Allies of the demigod Aviana and protectors of the winged creatures of the Broken Isles.
The coalition of orders dedicated to defeating the Legion at the Tomb of Sargeras and Broken Shore.
One of the last bastions of human power, this Alliance capital is ruled by the prodigal king, Varian Wrynn.
The Highmountain Tribe has dwindled in numbers over the years, and with the drogbar threat looming, seek new allies to save their homeland.
These are the chosen warriors of Odyn, sworn to his service in life and death.
The ghostly Court of Farondis and its allies continue the fight against an onslaught of invaders on the cursed island of Azsuna.

After Legion forces broke the Vault of the Wardens with the aid of Gul'dan, what few Wardens remain are determined to rebuild their prison and hunt down the terrifying beasts that were let loose when it fell.
The coalition of orders dedicated to defeating the Legion at the Tomb of Sargeras and Broken Shore.
The ancient keeper of the Royal Pond in Azsuna.
The watcher of fish in Val'sharah.
A master of the river and the fish within.
A raven with bright, intelligent eyes and a love of fish.
A mysterious withered who makes her home by the waterfalls.
Summoned from far away, Impus collects shells in hopes of creating a "magic gateway" to return home.
The oldest empire of Azeroth, the Zandalari are powerful trolls who bargain with fearsome loa and whose navy is unmatched on the Great Sea.
The island nation of Kul Tiras is home to Azeroth's finest sailors.
Free folk of the Great Sea, they know no loyalties but to their own crew.
A ruthless pirate band based out of Freehold in Tiragarde Sound.
Chronormu (Chromie for short) has always been one of the more active, approachable bronze dragons. Strengthening your bond with her will increase her power in the Deaths of Chromie scenario.
Princess Talanji and her allies fight to protect Zandalar from the onslaught of the Blood Trolls.
A special delegation of the Horde army, focused on disrupting Alliance operations in Kul Tiras.
Comprised of exiles and scavengers, the Voldunai use their knowledge of the sands to thrive where others would wither and die.
A elite special force delegation of the Alliance army, currently focused on disrupting Horde operations in Zandalar.
Masters of the sea and commanders of Azeroth's finest navy, the distinguished Proudmoore family has led Kul Tiras for decades from their seat of power in Boralus.
An ancient Kul Tiran order resurrected to battle the threat of witchcraft, the Order of Embers fights with knowledge guiding their blades.
Home to farmers, craftsmen, soldiers, and the mysterious tidesages, the Storm's Wake seeks to reclaim Stormsong Valley and affirm their place in Kul Tiras.
Traversing the world, the Tortollan Seekers wield their immense wealth to catalogue and preserve forbidden knowledge.
Enlisted by Magni Bronzebeard, the Champions of Azeroth seek to heal the wounds caused by Sargeras' burning blade and save a dying world.

After the fall of Argus, the draenei's finest warriors followed the prime naaru Xe'ra across the cosmos in an eternal war to bring about the Legion's end. Since then, other survivors of the Burning Crusade have joined the ranks of the Lightforged.

Although many struggled to oppose the Burning Legion's conquest of Argus, not all were able to escape. Emboldened by the arrival of new allies, these refugees and outcasts stand united in their mission to reclaim their home.
An unconventional crew of "mongrel" races based out of Freehold in Tiragarde Sound.
A crew of rough-and-tumble bruisers who never shy away from a fight. One of many pirate bands based out of Freehold in Tiragarde Sound.
A cunning band of sellswords and bandits who kill for the highest bidder. Between contracts, they drop anchor at the port of Freehold in Tiragarde Sound.
A shipping and manufacturing company based out of Boralus. Rumors around the Kul Tiran capital suggest this imposing company to be a front for a more sinister criminal empire.
The island nation of Kul Tiras is home to Azeroth's finest sailors.
The island nation of Kul Tiras is home to Azeroth's finest sailors.
A group of battle-hungry fighters has gathered creatures from far and wide to participate in bloody arena deathmatches with heroes of the Alliance.
Creatures have been gathered from far and wide to participate in bloody arena deathmatches with heroes of the Horde.
Oppressed by the Naga, these refugees have banded together to rise up and seize their freedom.
Oppressed by the Naga, these refugees have banded together to rise up and seize their freedom.
Hunter Akana is an experienced hunter with excellent survival skills.
Farseer Ori is a wise and formidable shaman with the power to command the elements.
Bladesman Inowari is a veteran warrior who commands the respect of the Ankoan people.

The Rustbolt Resistance holds the line against King Mechagon and his evil plans.
The Rustbolt Resistance holds the line against King Mechagon and his evil plans.
A species of bee known for their unusual size. While newcomers to Stormsong Valley, they quickly made their presence known to adventurers and insect enthusiasts alike.
An ancient species of deep sea warriors, the Waveblade Ankoan traverse the deepest and most dangerous parts of the ocean.
An ancient species of deep sea warriors, the Waveblade Ankoan traverse the deepest and most dangerous parts of the ocean.
A group of mogu loyal to the titan keeper Ra, they are charged with defending the Engine of Nalak'sha from N'Zoth's minions.
A group of mogu loyal to the titan keeper Ra, they are charged with defending the Engine of Nalak'sha from N'Zoth's minions.
A loose coalition of allies headed by the Tol'vir, the Uldum Accord was founded to protect the Forge of Origination from enemy forces.
